cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for automatic detection of motion-related artefacts in cardiac magnetic resonance (CMR) cine images using deep learning architectures. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of synthetic artefact creation in k-space and curriculum learning approaches also suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning architectures for classification tasks is a common theme in neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
